    "recap_headline": "University of Louisiana at Lafayette Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SAN MARCOS, Texas \u2013\nTexas State used a barrage of home runs and a 16-hit attack to defeat No. 25-ranked Louisiana, 16-6, and complete a three-game Sun Belt Conference sweep on Sunday at Bobcat Ballpark.\nTexas State (15-8, 3-3 SBC) scored in five of its six offensive innings and hit eight home runs to secure its first SBC sweep over Louisiana (16-8, 2-4 SBC) since 2022.\nThe Bobcats jumped in front in the second inning when Ethan Farris opened the frame with a solo home run before Jackson Cotton followed later in the inning with a two-run blast to give Texas State a 3-0 lead.\nTexas State broke the game open in the third inning, plating five runs on three consecutive home runs. Farris delivered a three-run homer, Clayton Namken followed with a solo shot and Chase Mora added another long ball to extend the Bobcats' lead to 8-0.\nThe Bobcats continued their power surge in the fourth when Dawson Park connected on a two-run homer after Manny Salas drove in a run with a double, pushing the advantage to 11-1.\nLouisiana got on the board in the fourth inning when\nDrew Markle\nproduced an RBI fielder's choice. The Ragin' Cajuns added two runs in the fifth as\nJosh Lim\ndelivered an RBI single and\nColt Brown\nfollowed with an RBI single to trim the deficit to 11-3.\nTexas State answered in the fifth when Salas launched a three-run home run and Park followed with another solo blast to stretch the lead to 15-3.\nLouisiana scored three runs in the sixth inning, highlighted by\nSteven Spalitta's\ntwo-run pinch-hit home run and an RBI single by\nJayce LaCava\n\u2013 his first hit in a Ragin' Cajuns uniform.\nSalas paced Texas State offensively with four hits and four RBI, while Park and Farris each drove in four runs.\nJesus Tovar (5-1) earned the victory after tossing 5.0 innings with three strikeouts and five hits allowed.\nJR Tollett\n(4-1) took the loss for Louisiana after allowing 11 runs on 11 hits in 3.0 innings.\nLouisiana finished with eight hits in the contest, with Brown collecting two hits and an RBI.\nNoah Lewis\nadded a double and scored a run for Louisiana, while\nHayden Pearson\npitched a scoreless inning in relief and\nCowan Alfonso\nrecorded two strikeouts in 0.2 innings of work.\nThe Ragin' Cajuns return to action on Tuesday (March 24) when they open a four-game homestand against in-state opponent Southeastern Louisiana before hosting ULM in a three-game Sun Belt Conference series from March 27-29 at M.L. \"Tigue\" Moore Field at Russo Park.\nFans are encouraged to stay engaged with the Ragin' Cajuns by downloading the #GeauxCajuns app. Click\nhere\nfor iOS/Apple platforms and\nhere\nfor Android platforms.\nFor the latest updates on Ragin' Cajuns baseball, follow on Facebook (RaginCajunsBaseball), Twitter (@RaginCajunsBSB) and Instagram (@RaginCajunsBSB) or check RaginCajuns.com.",
